technicalAssets.name: SAP Cloud Platform SAP HANA Service

description.small: Create and consume SAP HANA databases.
description.large: The SAP Cloud Platform SAP HANA service lets you consume SAP HANA databases from your applications running on SAP Cloud Platform or on-premise, via Java APIs and other application runtime environments. It provides in-memory and relational data persistence, and offers self-services, for example, to create new databases, to update your databases, or to trigger restore, while SAP is providing infrastructure and database platform operations. Moreover, you can use a variety of included services, such as geospatial information processing, advanced predictive analytics, and text-mining capabilities.

headlines.headline: Data availability and resiliency
headlines.text: In-memory and relational data persistence to applications running on SAP Cloud Platform.

headlines.headline: Manage and access HANA databases
headlines.text: Store your data in the cloud. The persistence services also perform tasks such as backup, recovery, and load balancing.

headlines.headline: Advanced data processing
headlines.text: Process multiple types of data for your business, such as text, spatial, graph, and series data.
